  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      61.32,
      602.23,
      575.45,
      647.83
    ],
    "text": "The low-level atmospheric disturbance in the vicinity of Sri Lanka has developed into a low-pressure area. Therefore, wind speed and rainy condition can increase over the sea areas around the island during the coming days.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      61.32,
      658.75,
      575.42,
      825.22
    ],
    "text": "The naval and fishing communities are requested to be attentive to the future forecasts and bulletins issued by the Department of Meteorology in this regard. Condition of Rain: Showers or thundershowers will occur at times in the sea areas around the island. Winds: Winds will be Westerly or variable in direction. Wind speed will be (25-35) kmph. Wind speed can increase up to 50 kmph at times in the sea areas off the coast extending from Galle to Hambantota via Matara State of Sea: The sea areas off the coasts extending from Galle to Hambantota via Matara will be rough at times. The other sea areas around the island can be moderate.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      61.32,
      829.3,
      529.61,
      844.66
    ],
    "text": "Temporarily strong gusty winds and very rough seas can be expected during thundershowers.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      0.9599999785423279,
      12.0
    ]
